JSONPropertyIgnore.java: Annotation class that can be used on Java Bean getter methods. When used on a bean method that would normally be serialized into a JSONObject, it overrides the getter-to-key-name logic and forces the property to be excluded from the resulting JSONObject.
Ground truth tasks: use annotation class on java bean getter methods
Program tasks: use annotation class on java bean getter methods

Paragraph: JSONPropertyName.java: Annotation class that can be used on Java Bean getter methods. When used on a bean method that would normally be serialized into a JSONObject, it overrides the getter-to-key-name logic and uses the value of the annotation. The Bean processor will look through the class hierarchy. This means you can use the annotation on a base class or interface and the value of the annotation will be used even if the getter is overridden in a child class.
Ground truth tasks: use annotation class on java bean getter methods
Program tasks: use annotation class on java bean getter methods
